{"id":"project-LICHEN-25hu","title":"app_identity: TOFU check assumes has_public_key invariant without assertion","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_identity/app_identity.c:210-215

The TOFU check guards against public key mismatch:
if (s_peers[slot].peer.has_public_key && memcmp(...) != 0) {
    return -EEXIST;
}

The s_peers[slot].peer.has_public_key check will always be true because:
- upsert_peer requires has_public_key=true (line 194)
- upsert_peer_key sets has_public_key=true (line 248)

This is an invariant that should be documented or asserted:
__ASSERT(s_peers[slot].peer.has_public_key, 'existing peer must have key');

If has_public_key were ever false (memory corruption, future code change), TOFU would be silently bypassed. The current code fails open rather than closed for security-critical functionality.

Low priority since the invariant currently holds, but an assertion would make the security assumption explicit.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"cleanup","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:41:33.11766Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:41:33.117689Z"}
